  <title>High-profile Brisbane barrister fined $4000 for contempt </title>
  <content>
A Brisbane barrister who claimed the $50,000 in cash that former Ipswich mayor Paul Pisasale was found with at Melbourne airport has been fined for contemptuous comments made to a magistrate.
Sam Di Carlo appeared in the Brisbane Supreme Court on Wednesday over contempt proceedings brought by Attorney-General Yvette D'Ath in relation to comments he made to magistrate John Costello in January last year.Photo: Jorge Branco
While noting all lawyers experience frustration at times, Chief Justice Catherine Holmes agreed Mr Di Carlo's remarks amounted to contempt and fined him $4000, to be paid within three months.
AAP 
